      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating the Qwen3 TTS VoiceDesign Voice API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To begin, ensure your environment supports HTTP/2 and JSON payloads. Obtain API keys from the provider dashboard and set up authentication headers. Use the base URL "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "https://api.qwen3-tts.com/v1",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for all requests. Implement retry logic with exponential backoff to handle rate limits, typically set at 100 requests per minute per key. Test with a simple POST request to the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/synthesize",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint using a sample text payload to verify connectivity."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "API Endpoints and Request Structure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The API exposes two primary endpoints for voice synthesis and management. All requests must include the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " header and use UTF-8 encoding. The table below summarizes the key endpoints:"
          }
        ]
